03:06.245 --> 03:07.396
(CHATTERING)

02:58.785 --> 03:00.032
Attention.

03:03.868 --> 03:06.376
At ease, gentlemen.
Be seated, please.

03:10.389 --> 03:13.322
As you've all probably noticed,
we're currently headed north.

03:13.362 --> 03:18.576
Tomorrow morning at 0500 hours, we will
be taking a position at Yankee Station.

03:19.117 --> 03:20.707
That means we're back in business.

03:20.747 --> 03:24.447
We'll be flying sorties over North Vietnam
to take out enemy supply lines,

03:24.487 --> 03:27.460
which means we have to
cross over into Laos.

03:29.091 --> 03:31.009
This mission is classified.

03:31.584 --> 03:36.148
No cards and letters to sweethearts.
No phone calls to family back home.

03:36.188 --> 03:38.969
–Is that understood?
–Yes, sir.

03:39.065 --> 03:40.695
No one can know.

03:40.887 --> 03:43.725
No one except Charlie
when we kick his ass.

03:44.723 --> 03:47.177
For survival
in the jungle environment,

03:47.217 --> 03:52.299
the smart soldier must understand
that nature is not a force against him.

03:52.395 --> 03:54.793
He has to make nature work for him

03:54.889 --> 03:59.109
by utilizing the ample natural
provisions at his disposal.

03:59.205 --> 04:01.123
Is this a double feature?

04:01.219 --> 04:02.082
(LAUGHING)

04:02.273 --> 04:05.782
For God's sake, just lean your
head back and open your mouth.

04:05.822 --> 04:07.165
What is this?

04:08.411 --> 04:11.344
Hell, the boys back home
don't know anything about the jungle.

04:11.384 --> 04:14.126
In the jungle, your best friend
is your knife.

04:14.166 --> 04:16.755
Oh, look at…
Now he's getting serious.

04:18.002 --> 04:22.029
Cut the leaf, man. Here it goes.
Come on, baby, cut. Cut.

04:22.317 --> 04:23.468
(SPOOK EXCLAIMS)

04:23.564 --> 04:25.003
(TROOPS LAUGHING)

04:25.099 --> 04:27.648
Where is the salt and
pepper shaker for that leaf?

04:27.688 --> 04:29.606
Chew it, boy! Chew it!

04:30.757 --> 04:33.826
Leaf good. Me like leaf.

04:35.360 --> 04:37.334
Maintain a constant state
of readiness…

04:37.374 --> 04:40.476
What did he do, sit in an anthill?
Look at him.

04:42.841 --> 04:45.966
And then, when
the rescue helicopter appears, make sure…

04:46.006 --> 04:48.787
Honestly, it's right
above your head!

04:49.650 --> 04:52.527
Jeez. Shake it, Pops.

04:53.966 --> 04:57.464
He's got a nice ass for a sailor,
I'll tell you that.

04:58.761 --> 05:01.063
I don't mean that in a weird way.

05:02.405 --> 05:03.844
God bless America.

05:03.940 --> 05:06.433
Are you a smart soldier?

05:07.105 --> 05:11.093
I mean, I just thought we'd be assisting
some South Vietnamese generals

05:11.133 --> 05:14.066
against a few infiltrators. Whole thing
would be done in three, four weeks.

05:14.106 --> 05:15.121
You picked the wrong time

05:15.161 --> 05:16.176
to enlist, Dengler.
–I know.

05:16.216 --> 05:17.902
No, but I just wanted to fly so badly,

05:17.942 --> 05:22.218
and everybody, they were telling me
all about the fantastic massage parlors

05:22.258 --> 05:24.327
and the go-go girls, everything, and…

05:24.367 --> 05:26.725
And what did I get?
Goddamn one night?

05:26.765 --> 05:29.506
–One night in Saigon. That's me.
–Yeah, and that didn't go so well.

05:29.546 --> 05:31.368
Gentlemen, next please.

05:33.095 --> 05:34.150
Okay.

05:34.725 --> 05:36.603
Hey, are there any mosquito nets?

05:36.643 --> 05:38.138
What you see is what you get.

05:38.178 --> 05:40.863
–Okay. Okay. I see plastic.
–Yes, sir.

05:40.959 --> 05:43.452
I see plastic there and how about…

05:43.644 --> 05:46.865
Are you able to give me two slices
of that plastic, please?

05:46.905 --> 05:48.975
–Sir?
–And maybe six foot by three foot,

05:49.015 --> 05:50.126
you put a zipper in the middle,

05:50.166 --> 05:51.181
and I crawl inside…
–What you're describing

05:51.221 --> 05:52.235
is a sauna, not a mosquito net.

05:52.275 --> 05:53.866
Not a mosquito net,
but it holds off the bugs.

05:53.906 --> 05:56.168
And you put some netting on it
so I can breathe through at night time.

05:56.208 --> 05:57.318
–You got it, sir.
–Yes?

05:57.358 --> 05:58.853
–Absolutely, sir.
–Okay.

05:58.893 --> 06:02.114
Now, look here. Look at this.
I have my boot on your table.

06:02.154 --> 06:04.799
–Why do I have my boot on your table?
–I don't know, sir.

06:04.839 --> 06:07.141
Okay, this is why. Look at this.

06:07.908 --> 06:11.264
Can you create a flap for me
in the tongue here

06:11.360 --> 06:14.677
so I could hide my American passport
inside of here should I need it?

06:14.717 --> 06:18.225
You know what, sir? Since you're my only
customer today, it would be my pleasure.

06:18.265 --> 06:19.512
Thank you.

06:21.334 --> 06:24.020
So, Charlie got his shit together.

06:24.116 --> 06:27.856
Now we have heavy antiaircraft fire
around Mugia Pass.

06:27.952 --> 06:31.404
Change direction and altitude
every seven seconds

06:31.500 --> 06:34.953
so the radar of the enemy gun
cannot lock onto you.

06:35.049 --> 06:39.748
Your secondary target will be
the intersection of 121 and 90.

06:39.844 --> 06:40.859
That's the Ho Chi Minh Trail.

06:40.899 --> 06:43.201
That's right, Spook, inside Laos.

06:43.296 --> 06:44.735
Now, one more thing.

06:44.831 --> 06:49.434
They've been using your radios
to lure our rescue teams into ambush.

06:50.010 --> 06:53.326
Now, don't get me wrong.
You go down, you use that radio.

06:53.366 --> 06:56.108
But if they're hot on your trail,
you scrap it.

06:56.148 --> 06:59.382
You scrap anything
that they can use against you.

07:00.367 --> 07:04.012
Now, this is Flight Lieutenant Dengler's
first mission.

07:04.108 --> 07:05.354
Yes, sir.

07:05.450 --> 07:06.889
(CHEERING)

07:06.985 --> 07:09.342
You're gonna be Spook's wingman.
You think you can handle that?

07:09.382 --> 07:12.028
I could not ask for a better man, sir.
But, please,

07:12.068 --> 07:14.138
could I ask you a question, sir?
–Go ahead.

07:14.178 --> 07:16.343
You know, Spook is such
a goddamn daredevil,

07:16.383 --> 07:20.851
could you please order him not to
try too hard to die for his country,

07:20.891 --> 07:25.841
but rather to let the son-of-a-bitch
on the other side die for his instead?

07:25.878 --> 07:27.700
Okay. All right, boys.

07:28.563 --> 07:30.147
–You all set?
–Yes, sir.

07:30.194 --> 07:31.248
Anything else?

07:31.344 --> 07:33.588
–No, sir.
–Okay. Let's go, go, go!

07:34.222 --> 07:38.921
Radar Kilo, 6195, position four.

07:39.400 --> 07:43.908
PILOT 2: Radar Yankee, 67279,
position two.

07:44.483 --> 07:46.649
–Heads against the wall. Come on.
–Come on, Diet.

07:46.689 --> 07:48.471
Come here.
This is what we would do as kids

07:48.511 --> 07:50.773
when we were out for mischief.
It would keep us out of trouble.

07:50.813 --> 07:52.979
But we would usually pee right now.

07:53.019 --> 07:54.801
–Can we pee?
–I don't really have to.

07:54.841 --> 07:56.184
I'm not gonna.

07:56.471 --> 07:59.177
But this will keep us safe. Okay, fellas?

07:59.732 --> 08:02.281
Stay out of trouble.
Come back in one piece. Good luck.

08:02.321 --> 08:04.240
–Come back, boys.
–You, too.

08:05.678 --> 08:06.637
(WHOOPING)

08:41.929 --> 08:45.342
Boys, get set to change
the altitude again. On my mark.

08:45.382 --> 08:47.109
–Now.
–Roger.

08:49.123 --> 08:52.423
Gentlemen, do you notice
the coastline down there?

08:52.959 --> 08:54.877
Welcome to North Vietnam.

08:57.083 --> 08:58.713
It's pretty boring.

09:01.398 --> 09:03.276
Boys, we got too much
cloud cover.

09:03.316 --> 09:06.550
Climbing again 280 west.
We're heading into Laos.

09:10.509 --> 09:11.948
Target in sight.

09:13.482 --> 09:15.113
Lessard, roll in.

09:15.209 --> 09:16.359
Rolling.

09:23.552 --> 09:25.087
Farkas, roll in.

09:25.470 --> 09:26.621
Rolling.

09:31.416 --> 09:32.855
Dengler, roll in.

09:33.047 --> 09:34.293
Rolling in.

09:50.885 --> 09:54.146
I'm hit. I'm hit!

09:55.680 --> 09:58.518
Dieter, you're losing altitude!
Pull it up!

09:59.516 --> 10:01.051
Dieter, pull up!

10:08.052 --> 10:09.970
Dengler, get out of there!

10:11.025 --> 10:12.655
Dieter, bail out!

10:14.094 --> 10:16.204
Dieter, bail out!

10:16.683 --> 10:18.793
I'm not gonna bail out!

10:19.081 --> 10:20.903
I'm not gonna bail out!

10:40.563 --> 10:42.385
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

10:50.921 --> 10:52.109
(GUN SHOTS FIRING)

11:39.065 --> 11:41.175
(MUTTERING)

15:48.415 --> 15:49.758
Oh, come on.

15:52.060 --> 15:53.210
Come on.

15:58.102 --> 16:00.116
Come on, search planes.

16:00.595 --> 16:03.760
Where are you?
Where have you gone?

16:12.104 --> 16:13.254
Come on.

16:20.735 --> 16:23.037
God, how can it get this hot?

16:52.671 --> 16:54.877
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

18:34.042 --> 18:37.782
(SOFTLY) Hey. Hey.
I need to go to the bathroom.

18:38.837 --> 18:39.988
I need…

18:41.522 --> 18:43.536
I need to go to the bathroom.

18:45.167 --> 18:47.660
Yeah. I need to take a shit.

18:51.688 --> 18:53.702
Hey. Hey.

18:54.949 --> 18:56.771
I need to take a shit.

19:08.471 --> 19:09.718
Oh, shit.

19:10.773 --> 19:12.307
Hey. Hey.

19:14.705 --> 19:16.623
Does nobody listen to me?

19:20.172 --> 19:22.761
Why doesn't anybody listen around here?

19:23.816 --> 19:24.831
Why don't you listen to me?

19:24.871 --> 19:28.435
I said I needed the bathroom
and now I've shit myself.

19:28.515 --> 19:31.296
Why doesn't anybody listen around here?

19:31.392 --> 19:33.119
I've shit my pants.

20:00.355 --> 20:02.082
(HELICOPTER CHUGGING)

20:56.459 --> 20:58.473
(MUTTERING)

21:04.611 --> 21:08.505
They can't hear us.
They can't see us through the treetops.

21:10.269 --> 21:12.909
It's not my fault. I didn't signal them.

21:24.463 --> 21:27.013
(SHOUTING) Don't ever, ever do that again!

21:27.053 --> 21:31.409
You better just shoot me right away!
Don't you ever do that again!

21:40.575 --> 21:43.548
(INAUDIBLE)

21:49.686 --> 21:51.796
(SHOUTING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

23:55.416 --> 23:56.663
(EXPLOSION)

24:03.856 --> 24:05.198
This is unusual.

24:05.294 --> 24:09.452
You American pilots normally attack us
earlier in the day. Sit.

24:11.432 --> 24:12.775
(SPEAKS GERMAN)

24:14.022 --> 24:15.364
No English.

24:16.899 --> 24:17.954
German.

24:26.297 --> 24:29.267
Why don't you admit
that you are an American?

24:37.998 --> 24:38.957
Yes.

24:40.683 --> 24:42.601
I am an American citizen,

24:43.560 --> 24:45.286
and I love my country.

24:46.629 --> 24:48.795
But why are you in this war against us?

24:48.835 --> 24:51.097
I never wanted to go to war.
I never wanted to go to…

24:51.137 --> 24:55.164
I saw enough as a child.
I only wanted to fly.

24:59.384 --> 25:01.302
Then you should sign this.

25:02.070 --> 25:03.756
“Condemning the imperialistic aggression

25:03.796 --> 25:07.496
of the corrupt and debased political
establishment of the United States…”

25:07.536 --> 25:09.126
What else would you call it?

25:09.166 --> 25:11.716
“…against innocent children
and the peace loving working classes.”

25:11.756 --> 25:14.462
No, I cannot sign this. I cannot sign it.

25:14.537 --> 25:17.375
If you sign this, we would be your friends.

25:18.181 --> 25:22.141
–You could be released in two weeks if…
–I cannot sign this.

25:23.073 --> 25:24.987
–It's against my…
–Your what?

25:24.991 --> 25:27.484
I mean, what is in here?

25:27.868 --> 25:29.210
What isn't here?

25:29.306 --> 25:34.190
I love America. America gave me wings.
I will not sign it, absolutely not.

25:34.773 --> 25:35.924
No way.

25:39.184 --> 25:40.527
Your choice.

25:52.899 --> 25:54.681
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

26:29.918 --> 26:32.315
(PANTING)

27:33.023 --> 27:35.132
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

28:08.028 --> 28:09.946
(MUMBLING)

28:50.034 --> 28:52.623
The quick have their sleepwalkers,

28:54.733 --> 28:56.459
and so do the dead.

29:19.093 --> 29:22.737
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

30:47.228 --> 30:48.283
Hey.

30:48.379 --> 30:51.352
–Hey. Hey.
–Hey, there. Who's that? Hello.

30:51.448 --> 30:52.791
Hey, you American?

30:52.887 --> 30:54.517
–What?
–He's American.

30:54.613 --> 30:55.572
(LAUGHING)

30:55.668 --> 30:59.025
Yeah. Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.

30:59.120 --> 31:00.751
Yeah, I'm American.

31:00.847 --> 31:06.409
My name is Dieter. I'm a U.S navy pilot.
And originally I was born in Germany…

31:06.505 --> 31:08.575
–Be quiet.
–…but I am a U.S citizen now.

31:08.615 --> 31:10.149
–Quiet.
–What?

31:10.245 --> 31:11.684
–Who's that?
–Quiet.

31:11.780 --> 31:13.698
Why? I'm whispering.

31:13.794 --> 31:16.191
–Little Hitler's coming.
–Who?

31:16.287 --> 31:18.301
–Little Hitler.
–Who's that?

31:20.315 --> 31:21.946
Who's Little Hitler?

31:33.071 --> 31:35.085
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

31:36.139 --> 31:37.194
Okay.

31:49.566 --> 31:52.470
Now, what the hell is this?
The Middle Ages?

31:56.183 --> 32:01.075
Hey, listen. Don't mess with
these guys. You'll regret it.

32:15.556 --> 32:19.252
–Hi. Dieter Dengler.
–All right, let's go. Give it over.

32:19.776 --> 32:21.426
Who won the World Series?

32:21.502 --> 32:22.901
–The World Series?
–Yeah.

32:22.941 --> 32:24.915
–I don't know…
–Hey, man, the guy don't like baseball?

32:24.955 --> 32:25.970
You don't like baseball?

32:26.010 --> 32:29.134
–No, I don't know. I don't follow baseball.
–I'm Yik Chiu Tuo.

32:29.174 --> 32:30.285
–Yik Chiu Tuo?
–They call me Y.C.

32:30.325 --> 32:32.052
–Okay, Y.C.
–Y.C.

32:32.147 --> 32:33.354
Hi, I'm Dieter Dengler.

32:33.394 --> 32:35.120
–Dieter Dengler.
–Yeah.

32:36.080 --> 32:38.149
We all flew together for Air America.

32:38.189 --> 32:43.535
Yeah, I'm world champion of bad luck.
But I tell you something, I'm undefeatable.

32:44.903 --> 32:45.958
Hi. Phisit.

32:46.054 --> 32:47.356
–Phisit.
–My name is Phisit.

32:47.396 --> 32:49.314
–Dieter. Dieter.
–Yeah.

32:49.410 --> 32:51.041
Procet Kam Phong Kit.

32:51.136 --> 32:52.479
–What?
–Procet.

32:52.575 --> 32:54.301
–Okay.
–Procet.

32:54.397 --> 32:55.644
What was that?

32:55.836 --> 32:56.755
–Procet.
–It's okay.

32:56.795 --> 32:57.754
Okay.

32:57.850 --> 33:01.686
–That was actually Procet… Got that?
–Right.

33:01.782 --> 33:04.139
–But you need to call him Procet.
–Okay, Procet.

33:04.179 --> 33:05.386
That's what we call him.

33:05.426 --> 33:06.345
He's also Air America.

33:06.385 --> 33:08.551
–Also got shot down flying supplies…
–Okay, okay.

33:08.591 --> 33:09.702
to royalist villages,

33:09.742 --> 33:11.908
–just like the rest of us.
–And when was that?

33:11.948 --> 33:14.441
Two… No, two and a half year ago now.

33:15.304 --> 33:17.798
–Two and a half years ago?
–Oh, yeah.

33:17.894 --> 33:20.930
I had no idea that we were here
for that long.

33:20.963 --> 33:24.415
Yeah, been here a lot longer
than people know.

33:24.511 --> 33:26.677
–Duane Martin.
–Duane Martin. I'm Dieter Dengler.

33:26.717 --> 33:29.842
United States Air Force. I was shot down
about a year and a half ago.

33:29.882 --> 33:31.568
–Okay.
–And when this war starts,

33:31.608 --> 33:33.774
we'll be here a lot longer
than we already have.

33:33.814 --> 33:35.540
Well, you see…

33:36.211 --> 33:40.911
How many more times you think
I'm gonna have to say,

33:41.102 --> 33:45.610
like I been saying and saying and saying
and saying again,

33:45.706 --> 33:48.679
that we will never go to war
in Vietnam, man?

33:48.775 --> 33:49.982
–No, they just…
–They, no…

33:50.022 --> 33:52.763
Because any day now… Listen.
They will what?

33:52.803 --> 33:54.681
–Yeah, Christmas come every day.
–They…

33:54.721 --> 33:55.736
They will release us, man.

33:55.776 --> 33:56.735
(LAUGHING)

33:56.831 --> 34:00.092
They will let us go any day now.

34:00.283 --> 34:02.161
–No, you see…
–Gene, by the way.

34:02.201 --> 34:03.736
–Gene.
–But listen.

34:04.791 --> 34:07.436
It's… The trick to it
is it's actually Eugene.

34:07.476 --> 34:10.545
–Okay, Eugene.
–Eugene DeBruin from

34:10.641 --> 34:13.039
–Eugene, Oregon.
–Okay.

34:13.134 --> 34:15.053
–How do you like that?
–Yeah.

34:15.148 --> 34:17.458
See how that works out? Name, name…

34:17.545 --> 34:19.712
Jesus Christ, not this Oregon shit, again.

34:19.752 --> 34:22.397
I've heard this over 2,000 goddamn times.

34:22.437 --> 34:24.603
–Eugene from Eugene.
–Oh, yeah, right. Eugene from Eugene.

34:24.643 --> 34:26.137
–You know what? You know what? Listen.
–Yeah.

34:26.177 --> 34:29.822
What you really need to know is
you see this man here?

34:29.918 --> 34:32.030
Take a good look at him. He, he…

34:32.123 --> 34:38.261
Listen now, he shits in his pants
every night without fail, man.

34:38.357 --> 34:39.603
Trust me.

34:39.987 --> 34:43.112
And you know the only thing that he
thinks is worth complaining about?

34:43.152 --> 34:44.975
You know what that is?

34:45.071 --> 34:47.179
–This man right here.
–Right.

34:47.275 --> 34:49.520
–Eugene from Eugene.
–From Eugene.

34:50.058 --> 34:51.016
Okay.

34:51.112 --> 34:52.893
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

34:55.812 --> 34:56.963
Dieter.

34:57.059 --> 34:59.800
Take a careful look to your right.
You see that guy there?

34:59.840 --> 35:02.773
We call him Little Hitler
for a very good reason.

35:02.813 --> 35:04.251
He is the worst.

35:04.443 --> 35:07.224
This one we call Jumbo.

35:07.320 --> 35:08.855
Oh, wow.

35:08.951 --> 35:10.733
That's the first smile I've seen
since I was shot down.

35:10.773 --> 35:13.418
Yeah. He's, in fact,
one of the only truly nice guys here.

35:13.458 --> 35:18.012
This is Nook the Rook right here.
He's also very much not a nice guy.

35:20.363 --> 35:23.488
–What is his problem?
–It's all right. Just keep going.

35:23.528 --> 35:26.173
His problem is he's Crazy Horse.
That's what we call him.

35:26.213 --> 35:30.625
And he is a bastard. Keep going.
And I just cannot stand him.

35:30.721 --> 35:32.887
–That's Walkie Talkie.
–Walkie Talkie?

35:32.927 --> 35:36.623
We call him that 'cause he does not speak.
Never, never.

35:37.530 --> 35:40.887
Hey, do yourself a favor, Kraut.

35:40.983 --> 35:42.477
Keep your head down
and your mouth shut.

35:42.517 --> 35:45.011
That's your best chance of surviving.

36:04.287 --> 36:06.877
So there is a war.

36:11.001 --> 36:12.727
There is a war.

36:25.290 --> 36:28.223
All right. So tell me about
the peace talks, man. Geneva?

36:28.263 --> 36:30.661
There's got to be peace talks, man.

36:30.757 --> 36:33.594
Shut up, Gene.
There is no goddamn conference.

36:33.634 --> 36:34.745
When are you gonna get that
through your skull?

36:34.785 --> 36:37.526
Secret talks, man.
I'm just talking about secret talks.

36:37.566 --> 36:38.813
Forget it.

36:38.909 --> 36:40.211
We're not getting out.

36:40.251 --> 36:42.417
No, no, no, there was a honcho
on the outside,

36:42.457 --> 36:44.527
he said I would not be here too long.

36:44.567 --> 36:46.349
They tell that to everyone
to get them to sign.

36:46.389 --> 36:49.075
No, I did not sign. No.

36:51.088 --> 36:54.925
Anyway, nice having met you.

36:55.596 --> 36:57.226
What do you mean, met?

36:57.322 --> 37:00.679
Well, my friends,
you can rot in here if you like,

37:01.830 --> 37:04.707
but I'm gonna scram this very night.

37:05.762 --> 37:08.064
This hut, it ain't no prison.

37:10.461 --> 37:13.818
Scram. I like that. I like that.

37:13.914 --> 37:17.750
Listen, listen, my friend,
you cannot escape.

37:17.846 --> 37:21.146
If you try to escape,
you'll screw up our release.

37:21.202 --> 37:25.574
Look, I don't give a shit about our release
or whatever you think is gonna happen.

37:25.614 --> 37:30.697
But without water, you won't survive
more than two days out there.

37:30.793 --> 37:34.819
And without water,
your tracks will be visible for even more.

37:35.396 --> 37:38.369
The jungle is the prison. Don't you get it?

37:40.959 --> 37:44.987
Hey, when does the rainy season start?

37:45.082 --> 37:46.905
Five months, maybe six.

37:47.960 --> 37:49.782
I can't wait that long.

37:49.878 --> 37:54.865
Hey, listen, let's say you do survive
the jungle and lack of water,

37:54.961 --> 37:58.757
whatever you find, snakes and animals
and shit are out there,

37:58.797 --> 38:00.675
you won't make it out of camp.

38:00.715 --> 38:03.421
There's six guards posted during the day.

38:05.606 --> 38:06.661
Yeah.

38:07.332 --> 38:09.059
That is during the day.

38:10.977 --> 38:12.607
I'm going at night.

38:21.142 --> 38:22.924
Why, what happens at night?

38:24.020 --> 38:24.883
No.

38:25.842 --> 38:26.801
No.

38:27.280 --> 38:28.239
No.

38:31.692 --> 38:33.898
I'm shitting my intestines out.

38:36.487 --> 38:37.830
Again.

38:37.926 --> 38:39.940
I'm sorry, I can't help it.

38:41.282 --> 38:45.023
You just shit right on my hand again, man.

38:45.118 --> 38:49.914
–Sorry.
–That makes it 2,207 times and counting.

38:50.010 --> 38:51.726
Leave the guy alone, okay?

38:51.832 --> 38:53.846
There ain't no alone, brother.

38:54.325 --> 38:56.339
Does anybody have a nail?

38:56.435 --> 38:58.217
What are you gonna do with a nail?

38:58.257 --> 39:00.999
You're gonna stab all the lousy guards
to death with a nail?

39:01.039 --> 39:03.340
What kind of plane you fly off of?

39:04.012 --> 39:06.945
–Procet has got a shard of glass, man.
–No, that's no good.

39:06.985 --> 39:08.191
I have porcupine needle.

39:08.231 --> 39:09.478
No.

39:10.437 --> 39:14.133
I've got a hammer and a socket wrench
stuffed up my ass.

39:16.959 --> 39:18.397
There's no nails.

39:18.493 --> 39:20.755
This whole prison's made
of bamboo and rattan.

39:20.795 --> 39:21.850
Damn it.

39:25.686 --> 39:27.700
I know where there's a nail.

39:40.839 --> 39:41.894
Okay.

39:43.140 --> 39:44.867
I'm gonna make my move.

39:46.113 --> 39:48.759
So all of you scatter in
all directions, okay? Go.

39:48.799 --> 39:49.950
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

39:50.046 --> 39:54.649
What makes you think you're not crazy
for thinking that'll work, man?

39:54.745 --> 39:57.102
Eugene's right.
It'll attract too much attention.

39:57.142 --> 40:00.307
Oh, for God's sake, that's what I want.

40:00.403 --> 40:01.650
Please.

40:02.417 --> 40:04.623
You trust me? Please.

40:04.719 --> 40:07.788
Duane, head to the outhouse.

40:07.884 --> 40:10.185
Y.C, go to the top right. Okay?

40:10.281 --> 40:12.871
Gene, please come on. No, no, no.

40:12.967 --> 40:17.186
Gene, Phisit, Procet,
head towards the gate.

40:17.282 --> 40:19.104
Move as fast as you can.

40:19.776 --> 40:24.000
Get their attention, that's what I need.
Go, go, go, go. Go, go.

40:36.847 --> 40:39.157
Hey, Jumbo, Jumbo. Hey, no, no, no.

40:39.244 --> 40:44.128
Can I borrow some of the toothpaste?
Let me get some of that. That's good.

40:44.807 --> 40:47.780
I felt so like having a good smile,
you know?

40:47.876 --> 40:50.582
Like you have. You got a good smile, too.

40:51.904 --> 40:53.055
Okay.

40:59.192 --> 41:02.453
Y.C., when I hit it, you make a noise.

41:02.645 --> 41:04.275
Cough or something.

41:07.056 --> 41:09.070
(COUGHING)

41:28.347 --> 41:30.169
(EXCLAIMING)

41:31.896 --> 41:33.142
I love it.

41:34.773 --> 41:36.595
I love it.

41:37.650 --> 41:39.760
I love it.

41:40.048 --> 41:43.692
I love it. I love it.

42:13.326 --> 42:15.438
(WHISPERING) Give me some slack.

42:15.916 --> 42:17.066
Let's see.

42:17.162 --> 42:20.519
Oh, God. Oh, God, that was an easy one.

42:23.396 --> 42:29.150
You see, I apprenticed as a tool
and die maker in Germany.

42:31.452 --> 42:36.439
There was no aviation at the time
and I wanted to learn something useful

42:36.535 --> 42:38.317
that would help me repair planes.

42:38.357 --> 42:42.961
And, boy, are those years coming in handy
in unexpected ways now.

42:43.056 --> 42:45.414
There's only one brand
that I cannot handle,

42:45.454 --> 42:47.104
that is Smith and Wesson.

42:48.427 --> 42:49.290
(EXCLAIMS)

42:51.208 --> 42:56.483
I think with practice, I can open these up
in maybe two, three seconds flat.

42:59.648 --> 43:05.498
But listen, everybody keep one cuff
on a wrist at all times,

43:06.553 --> 43:10.349
so that if the guards come checking,
we can put them on again quickly.

43:10.389 --> 43:13.610
No, they don't check us at night.
They think we can't get out of these.

43:13.650 --> 43:15.472
They think it's impossible.

43:15.664 --> 43:17.582
Show me how you did that.

43:18.637 --> 43:21.514
It's so simple. Okay.

43:22.185 --> 43:25.254
All you do, insert the nail.

43:25.830 --> 43:28.859
There's a cuff and a spring.
They both have teeth.

43:28.899 --> 43:33.118
You push down on the spring,
disengage the teeth like that.

43:33.214 --> 43:36.283
You see? This is what happens inside.

43:38.105 --> 43:40.311
–And the cuffs release.
–Wow.

43:41.654 --> 43:42.613
Hands free.

44:01.314 --> 44:02.465
Get away.

44:04.767 --> 44:05.822
Get away.

44:05.918 --> 44:09.658
No, no, no, no, no. Let him.
He's our friend, Malay.

44:09.754 --> 44:12.591
Let him do it. It's the best way
to heal sores around here.

44:12.631 --> 44:13.782
Okay.

44:14.165 --> 44:15.412
Hey,

44:16.467 --> 44:19.152
that cuff thing, that's good, real good.

44:19.248 --> 44:21.262
Yeah. Thanks.

44:22.509 --> 44:23.852
Hey, Duane,

44:25.578 --> 44:28.511
do you know where we are?
I mean, you have any idea?

44:28.551 --> 44:32.483
No. But my guess
is that this here's still Laos.

44:33.058 --> 44:34.977
And the guards, they're…

44:35.072 --> 44:36.183
–Laotian.
–… Laotian?

44:36.223 --> 44:37.910
–Yeah.
–Yeah, but the camp is Vietcong,

44:37.950 --> 44:39.484
there's no question.

44:39.580 --> 44:41.978
Look, I know what you're thinking,

44:43.128 --> 44:46.164
but jungles on these mountains
is a nightmare.

44:48.211 --> 44:50.513
Besides, you'd end up in Vietnam.

44:50.609 --> 44:53.254
–No, but if we can get to Thailand…
–Yeah.

44:53.294 --> 44:54.885
If we can make it to the Mekong River…

44:54.925 --> 44:56.899
Yeah, the Big Muddy.
If you could, you would, right?

44:56.939 --> 44:58.377
Yeah. We can.

44:59.240 --> 45:01.926
–Hey, why not? We can.
–Yeah.

45:02.022 --> 45:04.419
Just stop talking about it. Okay?

45:04.515 --> 45:06.433
Just quiet. Excuse me.

45:09.598 --> 45:11.708
–Hey, Gene.
–Yeah.

45:13.914 --> 45:17.174
Which of you guys knows most
about the country?

45:17.270 --> 45:21.586
Oh, that would be Phisit,
but he doesn't talk to us.

45:21.874 --> 45:23.408
What do you mean?

45:23.504 --> 45:26.093
You see, Phisit is pissed about…

45:26.957 --> 45:28.107
About…

45:30.313 --> 45:31.560
(CHUCKLES)

45:32.231 --> 45:33.630
He's pissed about something.

45:33.670 --> 45:37.794
We don't even remember
what he's pissed about.

45:38.465 --> 45:40.479
(SHOUTING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

45:51.508 --> 45:52.755
(GROANS)

45:56.687 --> 45:57.742
Hey!

45:58.317 --> 45:59.372
Hey!

46:00.331 --> 46:02.153
Hey, come back!

46:04.071 --> 46:05.606
Hey!

46:07.716 --> 46:09.786
I can't believe that bastard shot you.

46:09.826 --> 46:12.663
I know. I didn't even pull down
my flight suit.

46:12.703 --> 46:15.739
Hey, look, when I was standing
it looked like…

46:17.019 --> 46:19.032
We're gonna get even one day.

46:20.567 --> 46:21.430
(LOADS GUN)

46:26.705 --> 46:27.856
Howdy.

46:29.870 --> 46:30.733
(GUN CLICKS)

46:36.295 --> 46:37.734
Americali.

46:40.323 --> 46:44.255
–Americali.
–Americali. Americali. Americali.

46:44.351 --> 46:46.653
(LAUGHING HYSTERICALLY)

47:05.642 --> 47:08.135
Two years ago a parcel came through.

47:10.629 --> 47:11.684
Yeah.

47:12.547 --> 47:15.253
He puts it on display on really bad days.

47:17.054 --> 47:20.219
The bacon label still looks greasy.

47:21.082 --> 47:22.961
Does it still have a scent on it?

47:23.001 --> 47:24.343
Oh, you bet.

47:26.261 --> 47:27.700
Can I get a sniff?

47:27.796 --> 47:29.426
Oh, no, you may not.

47:30.385 --> 47:32.783
You may not. That is my sniff.

47:33.646 --> 47:35.852
Man, that is my sniff.

47:48.895 --> 47:49.950
Hey.

47:51.484 --> 47:53.498
How'd you ever end up a pilot?

47:55.128 --> 47:57.718
I always… I always wanted to be one.

47:58.677 --> 47:59.924
I was

48:01.170 --> 48:05.446
five years old, or something, in a little
town, Wildberg, in the Black Forest,

48:05.486 --> 48:08.747
and it was just bombed to ashes,
you know?

48:08.843 --> 48:11.879
No clear reason,
just these senseless attacks.

48:12.967 --> 48:17.666
But I remember I was in the attic
with my brother.

48:19.296 --> 48:21.022
We were looking out,

48:21.694 --> 48:24.859
and we see this fighter plane,

48:25.434 --> 48:28.791
beautiful, coming right at us.

48:29.750 --> 48:31.628
And it's firing from its wings,

48:31.668 --> 48:35.600
and I see the machine gun,
it's flashing and it

48:36.655 --> 48:37.975
(IMITATES WHOOSHING)

48:37.998 --> 48:39.492
goes flying past the house.

48:39.532 --> 48:44.327
It's so close. I mean,
it's feet away from the house.

48:46.149 --> 48:48.931
And the canopy was open.

48:50.561 --> 48:55.836
And this pilot,
he had his goggles up on his helmet.

48:57.082 --> 48:59.001
And I could see his eyes.

48:59.864 --> 49:01.878
And he was looking at me.

49:02.741 --> 49:03.988
Right at me.

49:04.083 --> 49:05.733
He's looking right at me.

49:05.810 --> 49:09.222
And as he turns to go, he's starting back,
he's looking right at me still.

49:09.262 --> 49:10.893
And the thing is,

49:11.660 --> 49:15.016
from that moment on, little Dieter,

49:16.167 --> 49:17.990
he needed to fly.

49:21.058 --> 49:23.072
You're a strange bird, Dieter.

49:23.648 --> 49:26.486
Guy tries to kill you and you want his job.

49:30.841 --> 49:32.183
Yeah.

50:01.626 --> 50:03.544
God, we need the rain.

50:04.503 --> 50:06.805
We need the rain to come quicker.

50:10.353 --> 50:15.340
See, here's what I can see,
you still need to understand.

50:15.436 --> 50:18.945
–No, I understand.
–You wanna talk about the rain again, we…

50:18.985 --> 50:20.807
Listen, now. Listen.

50:20.903 --> 50:25.506
We will be released
by the time the rain comes

50:25.602 --> 50:27.288
like I have told you before…

50:27.328 --> 50:30.549
–Stop telling me.
–I don't wanna have to keep telling you.

50:30.589 --> 50:33.559
–Then stop telling me.
–They will release us.

50:33.562 --> 50:34.617
You understand?

50:34.713 --> 50:36.495
And here's what I'm starting to think,

50:36.535 --> 50:39.412
that maybe you're trying
not to understand.

50:39.508 --> 50:43.440
If you try and escape, we,

50:44.111 --> 50:46.989
we will be killed,
we who you leave behind.

50:47.084 --> 50:49.730
–It's not just me, we all try to escape.
–Taking off. We who have been here

50:49.770 --> 50:51.592
for two years.

50:51.688 --> 50:53.470
Two years before you showed up.

50:53.510 --> 50:56.059
I don't want to escape alone.
We escape together.

50:56.099 --> 50:58.937
Wait, wait.
Why would the guards spend all this time

50:58.977 --> 51:01.718
cutting bamboo and wood
to build a watchtower

51:01.758 --> 51:03.444
if we weren't meant
to be here for a while?

51:03.484 --> 51:04.499
–Exactly.
–Two years.

51:04.539 --> 51:06.609
–Exactly. Why would they do that if they…
–Listen. Listen to me.

51:06.649 --> 51:09.582
–…didn't plan to hold us a long time?
–Listen. Here's what it all comes down to.

51:09.622 --> 51:13.746
I am not, I'm not gonna let you do that.

51:13.842 --> 51:14.993
No, no, no.

51:15.088 --> 51:16.775
You know what I am gonna do?

51:16.815 --> 51:18.349
I am gonna scream.

51:18.829 --> 51:22.195
That's right. I think
I'm gonna scream my head off.

51:22.377 --> 51:23.499
(MOCKS SCREAMING)

51:27.652 --> 51:31.584
'Cause see,
I would much rather they shoot you,

51:31.680 --> 51:35.036
than me, or any of us. You understand?

51:37.338 --> 51:38.297
Yeah.

51:38.393 --> 51:40.503
You understand?

51:40.599 --> 51:41.654
Yeah.

51:43.284 --> 51:44.915
You've been warned.

51:45.970 --> 51:47.216
Haven't you?

52:04.479 --> 52:07.068
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

52:28.455 --> 52:32.099
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

52:44.663 --> 52:48.211
(YELLING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

52:52.047 --> 52:54.253
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

52:55.308 --> 52:57.034
This is for shaving.

52:58.569 --> 52:59.720
Howdy.

53:10.941 --> 53:13.818
–Man, I can't get over it.
–What, this?

53:13.914 --> 53:15.928
No, that girl, you know?

53:16.023 --> 53:17.558
She smiled at me.

53:18.133 --> 53:20.243
And when she smiled,

53:21.490 --> 53:25.134
man, did I wish there was no war.

53:25.230 --> 53:26.189
Really.

53:26.285 --> 53:29.026
–I thought you were engaged.
–Oh, yeah, I am.

53:29.066 --> 53:30.849
We got engaged the day before I left.

53:30.889 --> 53:35.204
Marina, she is a wonderful girl.
So smart, you know?

53:35.300 --> 53:37.410
She studies marine biology.

53:37.506 --> 53:39.999
But I hope that she's waiting for me.

53:42.781 --> 53:45.234
–I'm sure she is.
–Yeah, well, she said she would,

53:45.274 --> 53:47.728
but, you know, women can be funny
and go looking for another man…

53:47.768 --> 53:50.165
(GUN FIRING)

54:04.071 --> 54:05.222
Duane, you okay?

54:05.318 --> 54:06.949
–Yeah.
–Y.C.?

54:07.044 --> 54:08.059
Yik Chiu Tuo, okay.

54:08.099 --> 54:09.730
Okay. Gene?

54:09.826 --> 54:11.264
Phisit? Procet?

54:11.360 --> 54:12.415
Yeah.

54:38.597 --> 54:41.186
(Happy birthday to you.)

54:42.625 --> 54:46.173
Happy birthday to you.

54:47.708 --> 54:50.489
Happy birthday, dear Dieter.

54:50.969 --> 54:53.750
Happy birthday to you.

54:54.325 --> 54:56.051
It is May the 22nd?

54:56.627 --> 54:57.778
Happy birthday.

54:57.874 --> 54:59.752
–Thank you.
–Happy birthday, Dieter.

54:59.792 --> 55:01.997
What kind of champagne is this?

55:02.093 --> 55:04.547
You just got to keep thinking protein,
lots of protein.

55:04.587 --> 55:06.025
It's not bad.

55:06.409 --> 55:08.327
Squished insect larva.

55:08.807 --> 55:10.341
(LAUGHING)

55:10.437 --> 55:11.588
Protein.

55:12.259 --> 55:13.218
Mmm.

55:14.657 --> 55:17.054
Oh, this is a good year, this one.

55:17.534 --> 55:19.124
(WHISPERING)
Yeah, my favorite.

55:19.164 --> 55:20.603
So, listen, guys.

55:21.082 --> 55:22.617
Thank you so much.

55:22.809 --> 55:24.591
And it is my birthday, yes,

55:24.631 --> 55:27.604
but I would like
to give you some presents.

55:27.700 --> 55:30.001
Okay. Now, look.

55:30.673 --> 55:35.948
I have taken these cartridge shells
and I have made a knife of each one.

55:36.907 --> 55:38.153
Okay.

55:38.249 --> 55:42.757
Now, I'm sorry, but I have to keep one
for myself. Okay?

55:43.236 --> 55:44.963
Duane, you're first.

55:45.538 --> 55:46.689
Right.

55:49.278 --> 55:50.429
Phisit.

55:50.909 --> 55:52.347
Left or right?

55:54.457 --> 55:55.512
Y.C.

55:57.238 --> 55:58.677
Easy money, pal.

56:01.074 --> 56:02.129
Gene.

56:05.198 --> 56:08.899
–Procet, it is yours. Okay.
–I don't care about the knife.

56:08.939 --> 56:09.953
This is for Crazy Horse.

56:09.993 --> 56:12.679
No, no, no. Crazy Horse is mine.

56:12.775 --> 56:15.556
My Crazy Horse. Mine.

56:16.515 --> 56:20.831
Now listen, we must collect the rice
and hide it.

56:21.502 --> 56:25.010
But we must dry it because it rots
too quickly if we don't dry it, okay?

56:25.050 --> 56:27.024
What? Hide it? You wanna hide it?

56:27.064 --> 56:28.367
–Yeah, yeah.
–We can eat it now.

56:28.407 --> 56:29.710
–No, no.
–We eat it now.

56:29.750 --> 56:33.642
Look, look, look, I've created
a secret compartment here for the rice.

56:33.682 --> 56:37.614
It is at the bottom of my crap container.

56:37.710 --> 56:38.917
So I don't think the guards

56:38.957 --> 56:41.993
are gonna want to check that.
–Crazy. This is…

56:42.217 --> 56:43.808
Why are you hiding it now?

56:43.848 --> 56:45.286
For our escape.

56:48.739 --> 56:50.273
You have a plan.

56:50.657 --> 56:51.712
Yes.

56:52.383 --> 56:55.164
Now, have you noticed

56:55.260 --> 56:58.289
that the guards when they are called
to the kitchen hut for chow time,

56:58.329 --> 57:00.303
they always leave
their rifles behind, always?

57:00.343 --> 57:04.369
So we have a few minutes
before they return for their rifles.

57:04.371 --> 57:07.208
We go out through the hut,
we grab their guns,

57:07.248 --> 57:08.455
–we surprise them.
–No.

57:08.495 --> 57:11.333
–And we surprise… We surprise them…
–Crazy.

57:11.372 --> 57:12.962
and we surround them, okay?

57:13.002 --> 57:16.839
Then we take the guards as prisoners.

57:16.935 --> 57:19.676
We take over the camp.
Think about it, okay?

57:19.716 --> 57:23.874
We hold it down for a few days
until we can signal our aircraft

57:24.990 --> 57:26.333
to pick us up.

57:36.978 --> 57:39.088
(SHOUTING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

57:47.720 --> 57:49.172
–Dieter, quick.
–Okay.

57:51.844 --> 57:53.758
They'll call mess any second.

57:55.008 --> 57:56.447
Quick, quick.

58:28.287 --> 58:31.932
–Who's in the kitchen?
–I see four.

58:32.027 --> 58:36.111
The cook, Little Hitler and Nook the Rook
and somebody I've never seen before.

58:36.151 --> 58:38.069
He looks like a villager.

58:38.165 --> 58:40.331
–What about the rifles?
–Okay, rifles.

58:40.371 --> 58:45.262
Little Hitler's rifle
and Nook's rifle in Hut A.

58:45.358 --> 58:49.578
And, okay, Crazy Horse
going towards Hut B

58:49.674 --> 58:52.167
with his submachine gun. Okay.

58:52.551 --> 58:54.333
There's somebody else coming up
over the hillside.

58:54.373 --> 58:55.772
–Who?
–I can't make him out,

58:55.812 --> 58:57.730
but he has a machete. Okay.

58:57.826 --> 58:59.168
Oh, shit.

58:59.360 --> 59:01.238
Nook the Rook is coming back
with his food.

59:01.278 --> 59:02.525
