01:21:39.568 --> 01:21:41.294
Where am I gonna go?

01:21:45.514 --> 01:21:47.240
Where am I gonna go?

01:22:06.229 --> 01:22:07.284
Dieter.

01:22:09.202 --> 01:22:10.641
It's gonna rain.

01:22:11.408 --> 01:22:12.463
I know it.

01:22:12.559 --> 01:22:14.669
This is how it always starts.

01:22:52.455 --> 01:22:53.989
(SCREAMING)

01:23:39.927 --> 01:23:40.982
Duane.

01:23:43.955 --> 01:23:45.298
Look at this.

01:23:45.394 --> 01:23:47.792
You see over there?

01:23:49.901 --> 01:23:51.148
See?

01:23:52.107 --> 01:23:54.121
Down there must be a river.

01:23:54.217 --> 01:23:56.327
It must lead to the Big Muddy.

01:23:56.998 --> 01:23:59.108
And then we'll be out of here.

01:23:59.684 --> 01:24:02.808
We'll build a raft, and we
can float all the way down to it.

01:24:02.848 --> 01:24:04.191
No one will see us.

01:24:04.287 --> 01:24:06.781
Then we can cross
over into Thailand.

01:24:08.507 --> 01:24:10.425
(CUTTING)

01:25:58.317 --> 01:25:59.756
Listen.

01:26:00.427 --> 01:26:01.961
Do you hear that?

01:26:04.359 --> 01:26:05.989
Is that a waterfall?

01:26:15.484 --> 01:26:17.977
Waterfall! Waterfall, bail out!

01:26:19.128 --> 01:26:20.375
Dieter!

01:26:22.005 --> 01:26:24.019
(SHOUTING)

01:26:31.883 --> 01:26:33.034
Dieter!

01:26:44.447 --> 01:26:46.365
–Careful!
–The shore!

01:26:46.844 --> 01:26:48.283
Grab the shore!

01:29:55.296 --> 01:29:58.173
Hey, pick a hand.

01:30:01.338 --> 01:30:02.297
No.

01:30:08.339 --> 01:30:10.737
Which one of your feet is worse off?

01:30:11.216 --> 01:30:13.326
That's a trick question, right?

01:30:21.286 --> 01:30:23.464
We can trade off with this thing.

01:30:24.930 --> 01:30:28.343
There's no way that
we shoot it out with the Vietcong

01:30:28.383 --> 01:30:30.109
if we run into them, so…

01:30:31.260 --> 01:30:34.956
And we can't use these for hunting
because of the noise.

01:30:37.494 --> 01:30:39.220
You wanna ditch them?

01:30:40.755 --> 01:30:41.809
Yeah.

01:30:51.400 --> 01:30:53.797
I'm sick of carrying these, anyway.

01:31:08.279 --> 01:31:09.526
(GROANING)

01:31:18.253 --> 01:31:19.404
Oh, God.

01:31:49.134 --> 01:31:50.285
Duane.

01:31:52.491 --> 01:31:53.642
We got to move.

01:31:53.738 --> 01:31:55.080
I'm too tired.

01:31:55.176 --> 01:31:57.574
–Keep moving.
–No, I'm too tired.

01:31:58.533 --> 01:31:59.971
Come on, buddy.

01:32:02.465 --> 01:32:04.287
I can't go on any longer.

01:32:40.347 --> 01:32:41.402
Duane.

01:32:42.936 --> 01:32:43.991
Duane.

01:32:45.142 --> 01:32:46.677
These are huts.

01:32:47.444 --> 01:32:50.992
This is an abandoned village.

01:32:52.814 --> 01:32:54.157
This is a hut.

01:32:55.692 --> 01:32:56.651
No.

01:32:57.034 --> 01:32:59.048
–Yeah.
–It's all jungle.

01:33:00.391 --> 01:33:01.638
Be careful.

01:33:22.737 --> 01:33:24.079
–I'm done.
–No.

01:33:25.326 --> 01:33:26.764
Travel by night.

01:33:26.860 --> 01:33:28.834
No, I'm telling you,
I can't go any further.

01:33:28.874 --> 01:33:30.792
You just leave me here.

01:33:32.039 --> 01:33:33.765
We'll travel by night.

01:33:34.053 --> 01:33:35.588
I help you along.

01:33:35.684 --> 01:33:38.521
When we reach the Big Muddy,
we'll make it across,

01:33:38.561 --> 01:33:43.164
and I'm sure we're gonna run right
into an American officers' club.

01:33:44.315 --> 01:33:45.905
And we're gonna go
straight into the kitchen,

01:33:45.945 --> 01:33:48.878
and we're gonna order a burger
and French fries

01:33:48.918 --> 01:33:51.700
and milkshake and ice cream sundaes.

01:33:52.083 --> 01:33:54.393
All that sweet stuff that you like.

01:33:56.591 --> 01:33:58.085
(HELICOPTERS APPROACHING)

01:33:58.125 --> 01:34:01.482
Duane! Duane! There's choppers!

01:34:01.578 --> 01:34:03.400
Duane! Duane, look!

01:34:03.496 --> 01:34:06.565
There's… Oh, here we are!

01:34:06.661 --> 01:34:08.003
Here we are!

01:34:08.099 --> 01:34:11.072
Oh, please! Please, be real!

01:34:11.168 --> 01:34:14.468
Here we are! It's your buddies!
It's your buddies!

01:34:14.621 --> 01:34:16.155
Oh, yes!

01:34:16.251 --> 01:34:18.649
Thank you! Thank you!

01:34:18.745 --> 01:34:21.430
We're here! We're here!

01:34:21.718 --> 01:34:23.060
No!

01:34:23.252 --> 01:34:24.691
We're here!

01:34:25.554 --> 01:34:27.376
Where are you going?

01:34:28.719 --> 01:34:30.157
We are here!

01:34:31.020 --> 01:34:32.555
Stop!

01:34:34.377 --> 01:34:37.158
You idiots, where are you going?

01:34:44.926 --> 01:34:46.077
Please.

01:34:47.803 --> 01:34:48.954
Please.

01:34:49.434 --> 01:34:50.968
Please come back.

01:34:52.215 --> 01:34:53.749
Please come back.

01:35:15.328 --> 01:35:16.822
–Keep your voice down.
–Duane.

01:35:16.862 --> 01:35:18.013
–Dieter.
–Duane.

01:35:18.109 --> 01:35:20.411
–The guards are coming.
–Duane,

01:35:21.945 --> 01:35:23.480
I'm not speaking.

01:35:25.110 --> 01:35:26.645
I'm not speaking.

01:35:27.987 --> 01:35:31.919
God, why don't you help us
when we need you most?

01:35:32.015 --> 01:35:34.892
Keep your voice down.
They're coming.

01:35:38.057 --> 01:35:40.263
(SHIVERING)

01:35:46.689 --> 01:35:47.935
Come here.

01:35:48.798 --> 01:35:50.045
Lie down.

01:35:58.101 --> 01:35:59.540
Lie down there.

01:36:00.978 --> 01:36:02.129
Lie down.

01:36:03.280 --> 01:36:04.527
Okay.

01:36:06.924 --> 01:36:11.336
Listen, I'm gonna build
a fire tonight, a big one.

01:36:11.528 --> 01:36:14.168
And those helicopters,
they will see it.

01:36:14.405 --> 01:36:16.121
And they will come for us.

01:36:16.131 --> 01:36:18.145
Okay, they will come for us.

01:36:24.091 --> 01:36:26.297
Come on, come on.

01:36:27.640 --> 01:36:28.790
Yes.

01:37:08.111 --> 01:37:09.741
Here we are!

01:37:10.605 --> 01:37:13.961
Here we are! Oh, yes!

01:37:14.057 --> 01:37:17.606
Oh, thank God! Oh, yes!

01:37:17.702 --> 01:37:18.852
Yeah!

01:37:19.332 --> 01:37:20.675
Yes!

01:37:20.770 --> 01:37:22.880
(MACHINE GUN FIRING)

01:37:30.169 --> 01:37:31.799
You idiots!

01:37:31.895 --> 01:37:34.005
You almost killed me!

01:37:35.444 --> 01:37:37.266
(SOBBING)

01:38:28.958 --> 01:38:31.260
I dreamed there was a fire.

01:38:33.753 --> 01:38:38.165
Why did they think a whole damn village
would be burning?

01:38:39.124 --> 01:38:41.234
How could we be Vietcong?

01:38:44.303 --> 01:38:46.317
Now they must've heard us.

01:38:46.413 --> 01:38:47.947
They must've seen this.

01:38:48.043 --> 01:38:52.333
The Vietcong will be on their way.
They could be here any moment.

01:38:55.620 --> 01:38:56.770
Let's leave here.

01:39:25.254 --> 01:39:28.898
(SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

01:39:34.844 --> 01:39:37.088
(MAN SHOUTING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

01:39:37.626 --> 01:39:39.600
(DIETER SPEAKING IN
FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

01:39:39.640 --> 01:39:41.078
(SHOUTING)

01:40:11.480 --> 01:40:13.110
(YELLING)

01:40:35.935 --> 01:40:38.141
(SHOUTING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

01:41:09.214 --> 01:41:10.653
Dieter.

01:41:14.201 --> 01:41:15.448
Dieter.

01:41:18.996 --> 01:41:20.531
My feet are cold.

01:41:42.109 --> 01:41:44.507
(MAN SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

01:42:57.873 --> 01:42:59.120
I'm cold.

01:43:01.901 --> 01:43:03.436
My feet are cold.

01:43:09.382 --> 01:43:11.108
You can have the sole.

01:43:24.535 --> 01:43:25.590
Duane?

01:45:08.878 --> 01:45:10.796
(DIETER SHOUTING)

01:45:13.098 --> 01:45:14.824
Hey, you!

01:45:16.071 --> 01:45:17.606
I'm here!

01:45:19.811 --> 01:45:21.921
Please turn around.

01:45:24.798 --> 01:45:26.333
Hey!

01:45:29.210 --> 01:45:31.799
Don't leave. Hey!

01:45:33.430 --> 01:45:35.731
Hey! Hey!

01:45:40.047 --> 01:45:41.678
Don't go away.

01:45:43.979 --> 01:45:45.514
Don't go away.

01:45:50.692 --> 01:45:51.939
Hey!

01:45:52.802 --> 01:45:54.625
Oh, come on!

01:45:57.118 --> 01:45:58.653
Oh, please!

01:45:59.036 --> 01:46:00.475
Come on!

01:46:08.627 --> 01:46:11.695
Okay. Hey!

01:46:12.175 --> 01:46:15.723
Over here! Over here!

01:46:15.819 --> 01:46:18.129
Help me!
Come on, come on, come on.

01:46:18.696 --> 01:46:21.286
Come on down. Yeah, come on.

01:46:25.697 --> 01:46:26.944
They're coming.

01:46:31.068 --> 01:46:32.986
Yes! Yes, please!

01:46:34.329 --> 01:46:35.767
See me!

01:46:44.207 --> 01:46:45.166
Yes!

01:47:16.431 --> 01:47:18.253
(DIETER LAUGHING)

01:47:42.229 --> 01:47:43.668
Who are you, buddy?

01:47:43.763 --> 01:47:45.106
Name?

01:47:45.490 --> 01:47:50.668
Flight Lieutenant Dieter Dengler,
U.S.S ranger.

01:47:50.764 --> 01:47:51.915
Authenticator?

01:47:52.011 --> 01:47:53.218
–What's your authenticator?
–Rescue Dawn.

01:47:53.258 --> 01:47:54.465
–Rescue Dawn.
–Louder!

01:47:54.505 --> 01:47:56.039
Rescue Dawn!

01:47:56.135 --> 01:47:58.820
–Favorite sport?
–Hunting.

01:47:58.916 --> 01:48:01.026
Favorite fish?

01:48:01.122 --> 01:48:02.177
Trout.

01:48:02.273 --> 01:48:04.151
Confirmed. Confirmed. It's him!

01:48:04.191 --> 01:48:06.301
I can't believe it.

01:48:06.397 --> 01:48:08.467
Jesus, buddy, you made it
out of the bush.

01:48:08.507 --> 01:48:09.849
Bring him home!

01:48:11.192 --> 01:48:12.918
He's coming home with us.

01:48:13.014 --> 01:48:15.412
–Oh, shit!
–Going home.

01:48:15.508 --> 01:48:16.754
All right.

01:48:20.878 --> 01:48:22.509
Way to go, buddy.

01:49:10.269 --> 01:49:11.995
Easy, easy, easy.

01:49:12.858 --> 01:49:16.488
Hold up here, hold up here.
Hey, everyone listen to me.

01:49:16.790 --> 01:49:18.189
–We're in charge here.
–Back up. Back up.

01:49:18.229 --> 01:49:21.450
This man has been on
a highly classified operation. Hold.

01:49:21.490 --> 01:49:24.327
No one is to see him. No one is
to touch him. No one is to talk to him.

01:49:24.367 --> 01:49:26.437
–Get him inside.
–You'll forget what you've seen.

01:49:26.477 --> 01:49:29.697
In fact, from now on, it's a
black operation. Is that clear?

01:49:29.737 --> 01:49:30.848
You got me on that?

01:49:30.888 --> 01:49:32.287
–Back up. Back up.
–Stand back.

01:49:32.327 --> 01:49:33.765
All right. Let's go.

01:49:35.971 --> 01:49:37.985
You're doing great, Dieter.

01:49:38.273 --> 01:49:40.287
You don't need this anymore.

01:49:44.411 --> 01:49:48.151
(WHISPERING)
Hey, when can I go back to my ship?

01:49:50.165 --> 01:49:51.508
I don't know.

01:50:19.799 --> 01:50:21.813
Okay, go, go, go, go, go.

01:50:24.211 --> 01:50:26.225
You guys are a lot of fun.

01:50:26.321 --> 01:50:30.692
You know, how many times I have to
tell you? I don't know the coordinates.

01:50:30.732 --> 01:50:33.186
Let's go back to the guards.
Tell me about their uniforms.

01:50:33.226 --> 01:50:36.447
There were some with red stars,
maybe they're Vietcong.

01:50:36.487 --> 01:50:38.692
The others were Laotians…

01:50:38.788 --> 01:50:40.035
Oh, no.

01:50:40.131 --> 01:50:41.378
Oh, no.

01:50:43.679 --> 01:50:44.830
Dieter!

01:50:45.022 --> 01:50:46.276
There's my buddies.

01:50:46.365 --> 01:50:49.242
–Happy birthday.
–That's my buddies.

01:50:49.434 --> 01:50:50.489
You made it.

01:50:50.585 --> 01:50:52.599
It's good to see you, Spook.

01:50:53.749 --> 01:50:54.900
Dieter.

01:50:54.996 --> 01:50:57.394
Norman. Oh, my God.

01:50:57.490 --> 01:50:59.655
Gentlemen, can you give us
a couple of minutes alone, please?

01:50:59.695 --> 01:51:01.213
It should be all right.

01:51:01.230 --> 01:51:03.819
I got a little letter from his fiancée.

01:51:03.915 --> 01:51:05.889
It's kind of personal.
You know what I mean?

01:51:05.929 --> 01:51:07.711
Keep it personal, Lieutenant.

01:51:07.751 --> 01:51:10.684
We're in the middle of
a highly classified debriefing.

01:51:10.724 --> 01:51:12.219
Will do. It's from his old lady.

01:51:12.259 --> 01:51:13.793
–Ten minutes.
–Okay.

01:51:13.889 --> 01:51:15.328
Thank you, gentlemen.

01:51:15.424 --> 01:51:16.479
Thank you.

01:51:16.575 --> 01:51:21.082
Hey, Spook, what's with the birthday…
It's not my birthday.

01:51:21.274 --> 01:51:25.960
Dieter, those two CIA dudes wanna take
you back to Guam for debriefing.

01:51:26.645 --> 01:51:28.850
You don't wanna do that, do you?

01:51:29.809 --> 01:51:31.344
I didn't think so.

01:51:51.771 --> 01:51:53.114
Hey, hold on, guys.

01:51:53.689 --> 01:51:57.430
Hey, guys, he's a bit choked up in there.

01:51:58.101 --> 01:52:02.473
You mind giving him just a couple of
minutes to sort of pull himself together?

01:52:02.513 --> 01:52:05.062
Yeah, it should be fine.
We'll give it a few minutes.

01:52:05.102 --> 01:52:07.116
–He's a good kid, huh?
–Yeah.

01:52:07.212 --> 01:52:08.746
–Thanks, guys.
–Yup.

01:52:17.474 --> 01:52:22.940
…Right, left.
Left, left, left, right, left.

01:52:27.640 --> 01:52:29.078
Come on, now.

01:52:30.900 --> 01:52:32.914
Hurry up. Come on, get him in.

01:52:34.065 --> 01:52:35.983
Get him in now, fast!

01:52:36.079 --> 01:52:37.326
Get inside.

01:52:50.081 --> 01:52:51.616
(WHOOPING) It's my day!

01:53:01.781 --> 01:53:03.316
What are we doing?

01:53:21.825 --> 01:53:22.976
–Hey.
–What?

01:53:23.072 --> 01:53:24.702
Where is everybody?

01:53:24.798 --> 01:53:25.813
–Where?
–Right here.

01:53:25.853 --> 01:53:28.211
Why the decks… They're empty.
Have they gone home?

01:53:28.251 --> 01:53:30.553
–Yeah.
–Yeah.

01:53:31.128 --> 01:53:32.239
They're on vacation.

01:53:32.279 --> 01:53:33.717
Is the war over?

01:53:35.156 --> 01:53:36.211
No.

01:53:41.869 --> 01:53:44.171
You know I'm in a lot of trouble.

01:53:50.884 --> 01:53:52.515
Boys, here he is.

01:53:52.611 --> 01:53:54.872
They kidnapped him,
they brought him here to us.

01:53:54.912 --> 01:53:57.941
The CIA held him for four days
but they can't hang onto him forever!

01:53:57.981 --> 01:54:00.379
Dieter Dengler!

01:54:06.325 --> 01:54:09.586
All right, all right. Hold on.
Hold on a second.

01:54:09.681 --> 01:54:11.080
Boys, listen up for a second.

01:54:11.120 --> 01:54:13.574
Admiral Willoughby's
got something to say.

01:54:13.614 --> 01:54:15.244
Lieutenant Dengler.

01:54:18.121 --> 01:54:19.847
Good to have you back.

01:54:23.492 --> 01:54:25.370
–Thank you.
–All right. That's not all.

01:54:25.410 --> 01:54:28.766
There's more! Hold on, fellows.
Hold on, hold on!

01:54:29.821 --> 01:54:31.220
So, let's start with the man himself.

01:54:31.260 --> 01:54:33.138
Dieter, it is just incredible
you made it home.

01:54:33.178 --> 01:54:36.544
Now, tell us, was it your faith
in God and country?

01:54:37.494 --> 01:54:40.043
Come on, Dieter,
you got to believe in something.

01:54:40.083 --> 01:54:41.673
I believe I need a steak.

01:54:41.713 --> 01:54:44.399
A steak! This guy needs a steak!

01:54:44.495 --> 01:54:46.565
We're grilling up a big old cow for you.

01:54:46.605 --> 01:54:49.578
All right. Hey, listen up. Hang on.

01:54:49.673 --> 01:54:51.935
Can you pass something on to the boys?

01:54:51.975 --> 01:54:53.566
You know, something you learned
during your ordeal,

01:54:53.606 --> 01:54:57.442
something to keep them going
no matter how bad it gets?

01:54:58.113 --> 01:54:59.456
Sure I can.

01:55:02.045 --> 01:55:05.114
Empty what is full.

01:55:06.457 --> 01:55:08.950
Fill what is empty.

01:55:12.690 --> 01:55:15.472
Scratch where it itches. That's it.

01:55:15.568 --> 01:55:17.158
Now look at these boys ' faces.

01:55:17.198 --> 01:55:19.116
Do they love you, man!

01:55:19.212 --> 01:55:22.664
Do they love you!

